caption: Super cute place with amazing food! I moved here from New Orleans, so I'm kind of snobby about po boys..... This place rocks!
Great food prepared fresh friendly service
Ordered the Whiting fish and chicken. It was cold and soaked in grease. The fries were soggy. They will not get anymore business from me.
The food is so good and I only been there twice.. yummy
The server was condescending when I told him that my fries were wet. He said, no sweetir I buttered your fries down." Ok well sir I don't like wet fries. His delivery was nice nasty and uncessary.

I usually visit the Surf's Up in South Shore, but I recently discovered this location which is closer to where I live. Friendly service, clean and the food is perfectly seasoned and fresh. I would suggest calling in your order because they seem to be pretty busy location, but I guess that's a testimony to how good their food is.

I am from Birmingham, Alabama and grew up eating catfish, collard greens, coleslaw, etc.. With that being said, my standards are high when it comes to good southern food. This place is outstanding! The manager and staff were amazing and the catfish was spot on. I will definitely go back to this establishment probably weekly now. I highly recommend eating at this restaurant!

The flavor was okay just a bunch of seasoning thrown on the seafood. Sadly I got more potatoes than anything and paid 30+ dollars. First and last time. The chicken and lemonade is really good though. Don’t recommend the card and shrimp combo. 2fish and willie joes give you two times more for the same price. Staff is super friendly just wished they warned me about the poor portions. UPDATE : Had better and more expensive. Your quality is not worth your price. Anyways guys my cluster was spoiled and I second guest it now I’m up with food poisoning. THANKS SURFS UP
The crab legs don’t have any seasoning the potatoes  was like mashed potatoes

Great food great service wanted a delicious po boy and I found it!!  Also have to give a shout out to the onion rings hand made in front of me and the fried biscuits which are better than any beignets I have ever had!!  Will be back for seconds and prolly thirds.
We made a company lunch order. Everything was delicious! Hennessy wings, Salmon burgers, shrimp & grits, fried green tomatoes. Going back soon
Their Hennessy wings are on point. Lobster po boys are awesome. I mean get whatever it will make you happy
Great food

Food was tasty and well-cooked, but I was a little surprised at how pricey it all was for mostly fried food and pretty standard side options. I ordered the fish and wing combo, and they were both good. Their cheesy grits might have been my favorite part of the order. The fried biscuits for dessert) were also very refreshing. I'll definitely be back to try the crab, lobster, and shrimp, but I do wish it was a bit more affordable.
Food wonderful and good customer service...
Excellent customer service and excellent food!

I’ve been doing my best to support black owned businesses in Chicago. This one! This one is special! I apologize for the presentation of this photo. It was at night and I used the flash on my camera. Also, the food was “to go” so the presentation is  subject to me taking it out of the bag… Considering that - It still looks amazing. What you are looking at is an entrée composed of fried shrimp and yes! #FriedLobster! Coincidentally, I found out that one of the chefs lives next-door to my cousin. He was amazingly friendly and let me know That I had the option of grilled shrimp or lobster as well. He also told me that I should try the house-made Hennessey sauce. “Hennessey sauce?” “Yes Hennessey sauce…” The owner is a uber-cute young lady (she bad) that looks like we could have went to high school together if I grew up in Chicago. She is amazingly congenial. I was fortunate enough to have her greet me as I walked in and give me a menu. Much success to her! Not much ambience in this place, although the outdoor seating is fabulous, and there is a section for a DJ and live music! Overall, the five stars that I gave this restaurant is for the sheer taste. I’m sure that this restaurant will become a Chicago staple. It is “a must visit” and *must return* establishment. I’ll put my 4,000,000+ views as a Google reviewer on it.
This place is incredible ... amazing food, I highly recommend!

I stopped in impulsively on my way back from the grocery store. I was really hungry and realized my kid and husband were likely not going to wait for me to make lunch when I got home so I ordered some fried shrimp. It was a big hit. The shrimp and fries are fried and seasoned to order.  I imagine opening during the pandemic was a challenge but I am glad they are in the neighborhood. We will return.
Good chicken wings and shrimps. Service Is AWESOME!!!

Don’t normally write reviews, but this place was surprisingly great. Hennessy wings were delicious, as were the fried biscuits which were like donut holes. Not too expensive considering the serving size and quality, and the staff was very friendly!

The fried food is delicious. I always get the fried lobster and shrimp combo. Their fried chicken is bomb as well. I will say they only get 3 stars because their grilled/steamed food is very mediocre. I got a crab and shrimp combo, comes with potatoes and corn and it was very bland. The seasoning that was on the veggies tasted like seasoned salt and cayenne pepper, not very good. I’d say stick to the fried dishes for the best taste. Other than that the atmosphere is great and I’m happy to support black owned.
A business that was needed in the Community.
The shrimp and crab combo was delicious!!!! Friendly service as well, I will definitely be back!

Okay! The Hennessy Wings are decent, but not for the extra $3.charge. Im not a cheap person especially when it comes to food... but paying $16. For 4 Hennessy wings, and 5 fried biscuits was not worth it at all. (Prices too high for the quality & quantity ) My wings wasn't  dripping in the Hennessy sauce at all (pretty dry) fries were not hot and the biscuits were okay. Again the food is decent. Ijs I had better 🤷🏾‍♀️ #OldTownPark

I was excited to support a black-owned business especially in the Old Town neighborhood that specialized in seafood. I ordered the grilled catfish and chicken wings. I was surprised to see the cashier without a mask on. My grilled catfish was mediocre at best. The presentation was not appealing and a little too salty. I did however enjoyed the chicken wings. I know they are working on all the kinks, so I will definitely give them another chance and order something different next time. I wish them the best.

Made an order for a work event. The food was very good! I tried to fried catfish as well as the fried shrimp po' boys. The Restaurant had an issue, but they were so quick to call and make arrangements to have food delivered which was awesome. Owner was so sweet and we were very appreciative & full. Deff will order again.

I was disappointed that they were not taking covid serious I had to ask the woman preparing my food to pull her mask up all the way. Needless to say, when she gave me my food the mask was was around her neck again. She did not have any gloves on either.  I paid for the food but microwaved it first, losing some of the quality. Apparently they didn't research the cost of food in the area because their food was not worth the money.  My first time and the last.
The owner and her staff make this a very enjoyable atmosphere! Excited to have them in our neighborhood!
We stopped by recently for lunch and it was delicious!  So glad to have a new business closer to our side of Old Town.  Excellent service.

Tonight was my second time at Surfs Up in Old Town. The first time I ordered the catfish poboy with fried biscuits and it was delicious. Today I ordered the lobster poboy sandwich and it hit the spot again! The place was very busy tonight so we waited around 30 min to get our food. We placed our order at 6:30pm. But the service was great and and the food was amazing! You can tell they really care about doing a great job and serving up some tasty food. Can’t wait to go back again. They’ve only been open about 3 weeks, but I’m ready to try some wings next time!
Amazing service amazing food

There’s zero social distancing taking place here. There have been large, loud crowds outside the restaurant on the sidewalk and street, and the business is blatantly uninterested in responding kindly to residents nearby who voice concerns.
Great food and a great experience. I wish they’d allow you to call in your takeout order beforehand but I understand. Will definitely be back.

Me and my dad went here and ended up spending 42 dollars on 4 tacos and tilapia and a drink they didn’t give me cheese or tomato and the food was not the best but we were trying to support black owned businesses but we won’t be coming back any time soon
